            "yt": "AtJElvBQkns",
            "title": "Looks easy… until you ride it",
            "description": "There is no shortcut on the Knokteberg. Often overlooked compared to the famous cobbled giants of Flanders, this 1.2-kilometer ascent is a silent test of endurance. Without the cobbles to betray your traction, the asphalt seems forgiving… until your legs burn and your lungs scream. Every pedal stroke becomes a small battle, and every turn of the corner reminds you that even a “simple” climb can break you. The Knokteberg may not have the fame of the Koppenberg or Oude Kwaremont, but it leaves no mercy for those who underestimate it.",
